.SH NAME
iconv_open \- codeset conversion allocation function
.SH SYNOPSIS
.LP
\fB#include <iconv.h>
.br
.sp
iconv_t iconv_open(const char *\fP\fItocode\fP\fB, const char *\fP\fIfromcode\fP\fB);
\fP
\fB
.br
\fP
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
Da \fIiconv_open\fP() function shall return a cold-ass lil conversion descriptor
that raps on some cold-ass lil conversion from tha codeset specified by
the strang pointed ta by tha \fIfromcode\fP argument ta tha codeset
specified by tha strang pointed ta by tha \fItocode\fP
argument. For state-dependent encodings, tha conversion descriptor
shall be up in a cold-ass lil codeset-dependent initial shift state, locked n loaded for
immediate use wit \fIiconv\fP().
.LP
Settingz of \fIfromcode\fP n' \fItocode\fP n' they permitted combinations
are implementation-defined.
.LP
A conversion descriptor shall remain valid until it is closed by \fIiconv_close\fP()
or a implicit close.
.LP
If a gangbangin' file descriptor is used ta implement conversion descriptors,
the FD_CLOEXEC flag shall be set; peep \fI<fcntl.h>\fP.
.SH RETURN VALUE
.LP
Upon successful completion, \fIiconv_open\fP() shall return a cold-ass lil conversion
descriptor fo' use on subsequent calls ta \fIiconv\fP(). Otherwise,
\fIiconv_open\fP() shall return (\fBiconv_t\fP)-1 n' set \fIerrno\fP
to indicate tha error.
.SH ERRORS
.LP
Da \fIiconv_open\fP() function may fail if:
.TP 7
.B EMFILE
{OPEN_MAX} file descriptors is currently open up in tha callin process.
.TP 7
.B ENFILE
Too nuff filez is currently open up in tha system.
.TP 7
.B ENOMEM
Insufficient storage space be available.
.TP 7
.B EINVAL
Da conversion specified by \fIfromcode\fP n' \fItocode\fP is not
supported by tha implementation.
.sp
.LP
\fIDa followin sections is informative.\fP
