.SH APPLICATION USAGE
.LP
Some implementationz of \fIiconv_open\fP() use \fImalloc\fP() ta allocate
space for
internal buffer areas. Da \fIiconv_open\fP() function may fail if
there is insufficient storage space ta accommodate these
buffers.
.LP
Conformin applications must assume dat conversion descriptors are
not valid afta a cold-ass lil call ta one of tha \fIexec\fP functions.
.LP
Application pimpers should consult tha system documentation to
